{"type":"text","timestamp":1773245311811,"sessionID":"ses_3225b056affeIKEEihnMYwMnTu","part":{"id":"prt_cdda80464001LmmnGJB3XA0tqA","sessionID":"ses_3225b056affeIKEEihnMYwMnTu","messageID":"msg_cdda7f760001R6vXgqMvy609Mw","type":"text","text":"All done! Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n### Commits\n\n1. **`fix(cli-bugs): validate --priority and --difficulty enums on features add`**\n   - Added `VALID_PRIORITIES` and `VALID_DIFFICULTIES` exported constant arrays to `src/lib/features.ts`\n   - Added `validateEnum()` calls at the CLI boundary in `src/index.ts` for both `--priority` and `--difficulty` flags\n   - Invalid values now produce: `Validation error: --priority \"bogus\" is not valid. Allowed values: critical, high, medium, low, wishlist`\n\n2. **`fix(cli-bugs): graceful errors for invalid YAML and schema in loadFeatures`**\n   - Wrapped `parseYaml()` in try/catch to produce `Failed to parse .features.yml: <reason>` for malformed YAML\n   - Added schema validation after parsing: checks that the top-level value is an object, and that `features`/`archive` are arrays (not strings, numbers, etc.)\n   - Instead of crashing with \"Attempted to assign to readonly property\", now emits: `Invalid .features.yml: \"features\" must be a list (array), but got string.`\n\n3. **`fix(cli-bugs): use outputError()/outputMessage() in features archive command`**\n   - Added `outputFmt` option to `FeaturesArchiveOptions`\n   - Replaced all `console.error`/`console.log`/`process.exit` patterns with `outputError()`, `outputMessage()`, and `output()` from `output.ts`\n   - Updated the call site in `index.ts` to pass `outputFmt`\n   - `features archive nonexistent --output json` now correctly outputs `{\"error\":\"Feature \\\"nonexistent\\\" not found.\"}` as JSON","time":{"start":1773245311810,"end":1773245311810}}}
