{"type":"text","timestamp":1773246747272,"sessionID":"ses_322435403ffe4OOvT8TwP2P2VN","part":{"id":"prt_cddbdf7c2002gboU00pfjwYzp7","sessionID":"ses_322435403ffe4OOvT8TwP2P2VN","messageID":"msg_cddbdebd20017aO5yVB6jnmQs6","type":"text","text":"All 4 subtasks for the `cli-bugs` feature are already implemented and committed on this branch:\n\n1. **Validate priority/difficulty enums on features add** (commit `3c8612f`): Added `VALID_PRIORITIES` and `VALID_DIFFICULTIES` arrays to `features.ts`, and `validateEnum()` calls in `index.ts` at the CLI boundary. Invalid values are rejected with clear error messages.\n\n2. **Graceful error on invalid YAML schema** (commit `a4f6a70`): `loadFeatures()` now validates that the parsed YAML is an object and that `features`/`archive` keys are arrays, emitting clear schema errors instead of crashing.\n\n3. **Wrap YAML parse errors with user-friendly message** (commit `a4f6a70`): `YAML.parse()` is wrapped in a try/catch that produces `\"Failed to parse .features.yml: <reason>\"` instead of raw library errors.\n\n4. **Fix features archive to use outputError() for JSON errors** (commit `b040942`): The archive command now uses `outputError(fmt, ...)` and `outputMessage(fmt, ...)` from `output.ts`, ensuring JSON-formatted errors when `--output json` is used.\n\n**Build status:** ✅ Typecheck passes, build succeeds (0.72 MB bundle).","time":{"start":1773246747271,"end":1773246747271}}}
