{"type":"text","timestamp":1773435915345,"sessionID":"ses_316fcbe54ffegvIvV0T61c4er2","part":{"id":"prt_ce903f312001aFsI8FmjIdos2u","sessionID":"ses_316fcbe54ffegvIvV0T61c4er2","messageID":"msg_ce903e72a0017hIu4nd7TG9unC","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nFix crashes, validation gaps, and error handling issues discovered during comprehensive CLI testing of the `wombo-combo` CLI tool. The work is on the `feature/cli-bugs` branch.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Use conventional commits: `fix(cli-bugs):`, `feat(cli-bugs):`, etc.\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n- Do NOT squash all changes into one commit\n- Do NOT push to remote\n- Do NOT modify `undefined` (the orchestrator handles versioning)\n- Run `bun run build` to verify after all changes\n- If the build fails, fix the errors and re-run until it passes\n- Use `portless run` when starting any localhost server\n- Read the AGENTS.md file for codebase conventions\n\n## Discoveries\n\nAfter a thorough read of the entire codebase, here are the bugs identified so far (the agent was in the process of creating a plan before the conversation ended):\n\n### Bug 1: `abort.ts` — TypeScript flow analysis crash after `outputError`\n`outputError()` returns `never` (calls `process.exit(1)`), but the code on lines 52 and 62 accesses `state.agents` and `agent.status` **after** `outputError` calls without a `return`. TypeScript knows `outputError` is `never`, but the code accesses properties of variables that could be `null` if `outputError` somehow didn't exit. The `state` variable (line 52) is typed as `WaveState | null` — after `outputError` at line 48-49, it's still `null`-typed in the subsequent code. This will crash TypeScript strict mode and is a correctness issue.\n\n### Bug 2: `retry.ts` — References deprecated `config.tasksFile` (line 95)\nLine 95: `console.error(\\`Feature ${opts.featureId} not found in ${config.tasksFile}\\`)` — `config.tasksFile` is deprecated and no longer exists on the `WomboConfig` type (replaced by `tasksDir`). This will cause a TypeScript error.\n\n### Bug 3: `history.ts` — Access after `outputError` (line 247)\n`record` is used on line 247-248 after `outputError` on line 241-244. Since `outputError` returns `never`, the `record` variable after the guard is still typed as `WaveHistoryRecord | null`. The `record!` non-null assertion on line 248 is fragile.\n\n### Bug 4: `abort.ts` — Missing `return` after `outputError` calls\nLines 48-49, 53-58, 62-68: After `outputError()` (which is typed as `never`), subsequent code still references variables that haven't been narrowed. While `outputError` does call `process.exit(1)`, adding explicit `return` statements after would help TypeScript narrow types and prevent potential issues if `outputError` behavior ever changes.\n\n### Bug 5: `set-status.ts` — Nested conditional logic bug (lines 830-856 in index.ts)\nThe `set-status` case in `handleTasksSubcommand` has a logic bug: if `!args.featureId || !args.title` is true, it enters the outer block, but then tries to use `args.title` (which may be falsy) in `const newStatus = args.title || args.status`. If `args.featureId` exists but `args.title` is missing, it falls through correctly. But if BOTH are missing, it enters the inner guard properly. The problem is the outer `if` catches the case where `args.title` is missing but then duplicates the `cmdTasksSetStatus` call in both branches. Same pattern for `set-priority` and `set-difficulty`.\n\n### Bug 6: `completion.ts` — `--status` completions use wrong values\nIn bash/zsh completion scripts, `--status` suggests `ready in-progress done failed cancelled blocked` but the actual valid statuses are `backlog planned in_progress blocked in_review done cancelled` (with underscores, not hyphens, and different values). The `--output` completions also don't include `toon` format.\n\n### Bug 7: No validation of numeric CLI args\n`--top-priority`, `--quickest-wins`, `--max-concurrent`, `--max-retries`, `--tail` all use `parseInt()` but never check for `NaN`. Passing `--tail foo` would result in `NaN` being passed through.\n\n### Bug 8: `tasks/add.ts` — `outputError` returns `never` but has unreachable `return`\nLines 53-55 and 57-59 have `return` statements after `outputError()` which is typed as `never`. These are technically unreachable code (harmless but noisy for linters).\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- **Completed**: Full codebase read and analysis of all 56 TypeScript source files\n- **In Progress**: Bug identification complete; need to create a TodoWrite plan and start implementing fixes\n- **Not Started**: \n  - Creating the TODO plan\n  - Implementing fixes for all identified bugs\n  - Running `bun run build` to verify\n  - Committing changes\n\nThe agent read every single source file but had not yet started making any changes or created a plan. The working tree is clean on `feature/cli-bugs` branch.\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Entry point and CLI routing\n- `src/index.ts` — Main CLI entry, arg parser, command router (bugs in set-status/set-priority/set-difficulty routing, missing NaN validation)\n\n### Config\n- `src/config.ts` — Config types and loading (tasksFile deprecated)\n- `package.json` — Build scripts, version info\n\n### Commands with identified bugs\n- `src/commands/abort.ts` — Flow analysis crash (null access after outputError)\n- `src/commands/retry.ts` — References deprecated `config.tasksFile`\n- `src/commands/history.ts` — Null access after outputError\n- `src/commands/completion.ts` — Wrong status values in completions, missing toon format\n- `src/commands/tasks/add.ts` — Unreachable returns after outputError\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-status.ts` — Duplicated call logic\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-priority.ts` — Similar pattern\n- `src/commands/tasks/set-difficulty.ts` — Similar pattern\n\n### Commands reviewed (appear clean)\n- `src/commands/launch.ts`\n- `src/commands/resume.ts`\n- `src/commands/status.ts`\n- `src/commands/verify.ts`\n- `src/commands/merge.ts`\n- `src/commands/cleanup.ts`\n- `src/commands/upgrade.ts`\n- `src/commands/logs.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/list.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/check.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/show.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/archive.ts`\n- `src/commands/tasks/graph.ts`\n\n### Library files reviewed\n- `src/lib/validate.ts` — Input validation\n- `src/lib/tasks.ts` — Task loading/saving/selection\n- `src/lib/task-schema.ts` — Canonical enum values\n- `src/lib/output.ts` — Output formatting (outputError returns never)\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — Wave state management","time":{"start":1773435915343,"end":1773435915343}}}
