{"type":"text","timestamp":1773436035642,"sessionID":"ses_316fcbe54ffegvIvV0T61c4er2","part":{"id":"prt_ce9063b0f002Xv1Arb1MmGQRPh","sessionID":"ses_316fcbe54ffegvIvV0T61c4er2","messageID":"msg_ce9063023001qXOlAmzroKZvh2","type":"text","text":"### Bug 5: Fix set-status/set-priority/set-difficulty routing in index.ts\n\nThe problem is: when `args.title` is falsy, the outer `if (!args.featureId || !args.title)` enters, then tries to build `newStatus` from the potentially-falsy `args.title`. If `args.featureId` exists but `args.title` doesn't, the inner check works. But if both have values, it falls through to the `else` branch. The real issue is the duplicated `cmdTasksSetStatus` call. Let me simplify the logic:","time":{"start":1773436035641,"end":1773436035641}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773436036205,"sessionID":"ses_316fcbe54ffegvIvV0T61c4er2","part":{"id":"prt_ce9064773001M0sVJwA2zAyuMf","sessionID":"ses_316fcbe54ffegvIvV0T61c4er2","messageID":"msg_ce9063023001qXOlAmzroKZvh2","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01Y5XSyFmLzkr37MqznFf8pq","tool":"edit","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-cli-bugs/src/index.ts","newString":"    case \"set-status\": {\n      // The new status can come from the second positional (stored in args.title)\n      // or from the --status flag\n      const newStatus = args.title || args.status;\n      if (!args.featureId || !newStatus) {\n        console.error(\"Usage: woco tasks set-status <task-id> <status>\");\n        process.exit(1);\n        return;\n      }\n      await cmdTasksSetStatus({\n        projectRoot,\n        config,\n        featureId: args.featureId,\n        newStatus,\n        outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n        dryRun: args.dryRun,\n      });\n      break;\n    }","oldString":"    case \"set-status\": {\n      if (!args.featureId || !args.title) {\n        // title holds the second positional arg (the status value)\n        // If not provided via positional, check --status flag\n        const newStatus = args.title || args.status;\n        if (!args.featureId || !newStatus) {\n          console.error(\"Usage: woco tasks set-status <task-id> <status>\");\n          process.exit(1);\n          return;\n        }\n        await cmdTasksSetStatus({\n          projectRoot,\n          config,\n          featureId: args.featureId,\n          newStatus,\n          outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n          dryRun: args.dryRun,\n        });\n      } else {\n        await cmdTasksSetStatus({\n          projectRoot,\n          config,\n          featureId: args.featureId,\n          newStatus: args.title, // second positional = new status\n          outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n          dryRun: args.dryRun,\n        });\n      }\n      brea